1
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,360
Chaba.

2
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,360
Where are you off to?

3
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:16,320
I'm exhausted.

4
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,800
I thought you said we're gonna go chill.

5
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,280
This is not chilling!

6
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,440
There's Lord Grandfather in this jungle.

7
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:22,720
We must ask for his blessings.

8
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:25,160
He will give us everything we want!

9
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:27,680
Is there really Lord Grandfather?

10
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,600
Lord Grandfather!

11
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,560
Please tell me who the hell Glam is.

12
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,400
The one you two are looking for...

13
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,480
will change your destinies forever.

14
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:36,480
Shit!

15
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:39,480
I'll remove that mask of yours, Glam!

16
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:46,680
Here's your coffee, Madam.

17
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,440
Madam, you don't have to pay respect to me.

18
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:53,080
It's my job.

19
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,320
I didn't pay respect to you.

20
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:56,280
I'm paying respect to that.

21
00:01:56,280 --> 00:02:00,080
Shit, what the hell...

22
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:02,480
That's the Zebra Shrine. You think it's Moodeng?

23
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,880
Well, I know that but...

24
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,680
why is he so big?

25
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:10,240
I'm going to bring him to fulfill my vows.

26
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:12,240
If I put him outside,

27
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:13,440
he'd be in the sun.

28
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,440
So I put him here, inside.

29
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:17,520
Well, how did you bring him in?

30
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:20,440
Well, I got rid of the door.

31
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:22,600
That's really easy. How could you not think of that?

32
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,800
You got rid of the door?

33
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,000
Well, he couldn't get in because of the door.

34
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,040
So I got rid of it but I already replaced it.

35
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:30,080
But you have to bring him out to fulfill the vows,

36
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,040
and put him in the main shrine...

37
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,440
Oh, that's right.

38
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,440
Then, you gotta get rid of the door again?

39
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:40,040
Damn, I can see this airline's future now.

40
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,040
I heard that!

41
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,800
Hello, Mr. Yuttachai.

42
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,680
Hello, Madam Porn, the Beauty.

43
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,240
Why are you acting all wild now at this age?

44
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,280
Acting wild?

45
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,680
Well, you're talking to a guy now.

46
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:57,160
You got a boyfriend?

47
00:02:57,160 --> 00:03:00,040
Boyfriend, my ass. I'm talking to ChatGPT.

48
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:03,960
Whoa, are you that lonely? You rely on an AI now.

49
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:07,960
Madam, if you need to talk about something, you can always talk to me.

50
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,000
I'm asking him about Glam.

51
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Er, Mr. Yuttachai, I'd like to an info on Glam.

52
00:03:15,680 --> 00:03:18,680
I'm sorry, I don't have any information on Glam.

53
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,640
I feel sorry for you...even ChatGPT wouldn't help you.

54
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:26,000
But I have someone that may be able to help you, Madam Porn, the Beauty.

55
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,280
Who's that?

56
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,280
Opportunities like this don’t come often.

57
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:32,040
Once in two hundred years do you get to meet Lord Grandfather.

58
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:34,360
He lives deep in the southern forest.

59
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,440
Whatever you want to know, he has the answers.

60
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,200
But only if your merit matches his.

61
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,120
So don’t forget to keep your precepts and make merit regularly.

62
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:44,440
There you go!

63
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,040
That's my hope.

64
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,920
Now, I'll get to know...

65
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:50,640
who the real Glam really is.

66
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:53,600
I thought using technology would make things more modern.

67
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,600
Turns out it’s even more intense than before.

68
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,320
I heard that!

69
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,640
Alright...

70
00:03:57,640 --> 00:04:01,160
Alright, let's get ready to our journey.

71
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:05,160
This time, you'll get to go somewhere farther than Ang-Thong.

72
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,960
Please fasten your seatbelt.

73
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,280
Tighten your seatbelt, please.

74
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:30,640
I'd like to have one Carbonara, please.

75
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,920
Of course.

76
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,160
I want the pasta to be fresh.

77
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,920
Boil it in the room-temperature water.

78
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,880
And when you knead the dough, use your hands, okay?

79
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,880
And the bacon, I want it to be plant-based protein.

80
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:41,880
Damn, Chaba.

81
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:46,160
You're so picky when you're a passenger.

82
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,360
What? I just wanna be dramatic too.

83
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,400
Like, the ultimate diva, you know.

84
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,800
Sky, let me ask you something...

85
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:54,800
Don't you think about switching seats for us?

86
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,240
It's so hot here. It's all cramped up.

87
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,680
I'm about to burst into flames.

88
00:04:57,680 --> 00:05:00,640
Seriously, can you tell the captain to turn up the A/C?

89
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,000
Yeah, or do you have a fan?

90
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,440
Right.

91
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,840
A big one. Set it on level three.

92
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:04,720
Put it right here. Set it on level one, two, three...

93
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:09,360
Mmm, sir, by the window, what would you like?

94
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:12,480
Excuse me, are you blind?

95
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,600
I'm a madam.

96
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,720
That's right.

97
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:15,640
Can you not tell?

98
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,120
I'd like a chicken breast smoothie.

99
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:21,080
But only chicken born on a Monday night.

100
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:23,160
And from the happy ones farm only, okay?

101
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:26,440
No skin, no seasoning, sixty grams of protein.

102
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,080
If not, don't even think I'll eat it.

103
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,560
That's from someone who takes the protein very seriously.

104
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:34,400
Er, and you, our fancy gentleman?

105
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,920
I'll have something simple,

106
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,920
A fruit smoothie will do.

107
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:43,440
That's really simple. Got it.

108
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:45,760
But the fruit has to be cute.

109
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,640
I want Malabar almond...

110
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:49,320
passion fruit...

111
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,520
And krabok, okay?

112
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:55,520
Oh, and when you blend it, only use your right hand.

113
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,760
And whoever's blending it better not have been born in the Year of the Horse.

114
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,320
Bad astrological match for me.

115
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:02,160
We only got tap water, you want it?

116
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,160
Yes.

117
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,440
So where are you all off to?

118
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:08,120
Listen up, it's an exclusive trip.

119
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,320
For special guests only.

120
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:14,320
Country bumpkins like you wouldn't get it.

121
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,640
Wanna come along?

122
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,640
I can't. I have to fly.

123
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:22,680
Ladies and gentlemen, Glamorous Airline would like to welcome you onboard.

124
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,760
We'll now demonstrate how to use the equipment...

125
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:26,600
in case of emergency.

126
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,640
Everyone, ready or not?

127
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:30,280
Ready!

128
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:34,080
This is your seatbelt.

129
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:39,680
Insert the metal fitting into the buckle.

130
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,280
Tighten the seatbelt by pulling the strap.

131
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,280
Tighten it!

132
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,960
In case of decompression,

133
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:48,240
oxygen mask will be automatically...

134
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,960
changed into a Tuxedo Mask.

135
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,960
And transform!

136
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:57,160
I'm tired of you assholes, seriously.

137
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,520
Just being a flight attendant is exhausting enough.

138
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,640
What the hell are you even doing here?

139
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:00,640
Go play at home.

140
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,440
What a trashy flight attendant! Such filthy language!

141
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,120
Guys, let's ditch this one!

142
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:07,120
We don't want you! We don't want you!

143
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:09,880
She's crying now.

144
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,400
Fine, I'll be the flight attendant.

145
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:13,800
Yeah, off you go.

146
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,800
Everyone, line up straight!

147
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:32,120
Ah, it's so hot!

148
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,840
My armpits are soaked!

149
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:36,000
Oh, mosquitoes! They're biting everywhere!

150
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,200
Stop complaining already, Sigma.

151
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,480
We're all tired here.

152
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,520
It's so hot in here.

153
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:40,680
I'm boiling too, okay?

154
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:42,560
I can't do this anymore.

155
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:45,880
You should be hot, just look at you!

156
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:46,800
You look insane.

157
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,560
I'm not insane.

158
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:51,240
Don't you get it? We dressed up because we're models.

159
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:51,840
Yes!

160
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:55,840
Never heard of "Make every day a runway."?

161
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,640
We've been walking through 50 mountains.

162
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,720
This tree, I remember it. We've passed it already.

163
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,200
Right, I remember it too.

164
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:02,960
Which one?

165
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,600
This one.

166
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,160
C'mon, guys!

167
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,080
It's all green here. It's the woods.

168
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:11,040
We've been here already. I'm not walking anymore.

169
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,600
Anyone wants to go, go ahead.

170
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,560
I can't do it either. I'm too tired.

171
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,320
We're exhausted, we need to rest.

172
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,280
Okay, to lift your spirits...

173
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,400
I'll go find something for you to eat.

174
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:19,800
Alright.

175
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,080
What do you want?

176
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,560
Can we get something like grilled pork buffet?

177
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:27,320
C'mon, I'm not Hanuman who can conjure food out of thin air.

178
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:29,200
I'll go find some wild fruit for you to eat.

179
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,720
Hey, is it even safe to eat?

180
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,600
I don't know either.

181
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,200
Anything too wild and I'm terrified.

182
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:34,840
Oh, god...

183
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:38,560
Don't worry about anything, look at your outfit first.

184
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:41,360
He roams every corner of the jungle.

185
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:45,200
A nameless warrior of the Land of Smiles.

186
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,200
Hey!

187
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,440
Hey!

188
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,040
A mangosteen!

189
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,520
It comes with a hook like this?

190
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:53,080
Yeah, it must be one of a kind in a jungle like this.

191
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:53,680
Oh my god.

192
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,400
This must be an imported stuff.

193
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,720
Hold on, I’ll go get more for you.

194
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,200
Here, let Sigma have this one.

195
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,080
Sigma, here’s another one for you.

196
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,240
I’m getting dizzy.

197
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,920
Here, I got it.

198
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:05,000
So you guys feel better.

199
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Hey.

200
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,160
A strawberry!

201
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:08,160
From USA for sure.

202
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,360
Hey, we don’t need to leave the jungle.

203
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,400
Let’s just pick these fruits and sell them.

204
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:17,120
Oh my dear friend, surprise.

205
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,200
Huh?

206
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,160
Watermelon...

207
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,280
How did that get here?

208
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,280
Let me ask you straight.

209
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,680
Is it from Or Tor Kor Market or not?

210
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:24,440
Nope.

211
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,120
Did you make a deal with some vendor?

212
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,120
No.

213
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,640
Wait, hold on.

214
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,520
How are we even going to eat this?

215
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,520
We don’t have the skills.

216
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,160
Not a problem. Here.

217
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,880
I’ve got the equipment.

218
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:35,960
Let me see.

219
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:37,760
A knife.

220
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,000
There you go.

221
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,560
Wow.

222
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,640
Damn, it looks juicy.

223
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,320
Since you found it, you take this part.

224
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,120
Okay.

225
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,200
Sigma, you eat the knife.

226
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,000
Oh.

227
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:47,560
I have something else.

228
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,680
What is it?

229
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,480
A spoon.

230
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,040
Let me ask you something.

231
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:56,520
Yeah.

232
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,080
Didn’t you say this was a chill trip?

233
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:01,080
Like a laid-back Western-influencer vibe?

234
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,120
This is not it anymore.

235
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:06,200
Hey, come on. Don’t be mad.

236
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,840
Sigma, tell me.

237
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:10,040
Are you that mad?

238
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,160
I’m really mad.

239
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,840
Fine, I’ll tell you.

240
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,520
The reason I came here.

241
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:19,040
I didn’t come here for some adventure trip.

242
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:21,600
I came here for a spiritual ritual.

243
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,280
What? Why didn’t you say so from the start?

244
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,880
Because this forest has Lord Grandfather.

245
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,480
Half man, half tiger.

246
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,240
He lives deep in the jungle.

247
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,840
We have to ask for his blessing.

248
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,880
Because he can create anything for us.

249
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:35,760
Hey.

250
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,760
I came here to ask Lord Grandfather for a blessing.

251
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:42,760
So that I and all of us can walk on the world’s plus-size supermodel stage.

252
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,240
It’s our dream, you know.

253
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,240
Exactly.

254
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,720
Is it far from here...

255
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,400
...until we get to Lord Grandfather or whatever?

256
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:52,720
Not too far. See that mountain?

257
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,640
Oh wow.

258
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:56,440
We'll just have to walk to that mountain.

259
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:59,080
Then we’ll see a wide stream.

260
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:02,480
We’ll swim across it for another seven kilometers.

261
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:06,040
Then hike about fifteen more kilometers.

262
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:09,200
And then we’ll reach Lord Grandfather’s cave.

263
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,080
Then I’m heading back.

264
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:10,520
Don’t go.

265
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,000
Wait, wait, wait.

266
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,200
I can’t walk anymore.

267
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,480
Is Lord Grandfather even real?

268
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,480
Oh my god. Lord Grandfather is real!

269
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,080
It’s nothing, don’t be scared.

270
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:24,520
Your hat just fell over your eyes.

271
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:25,800
I’m scared of Lord Grandfather.

272
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:26,480
Don’t be scared.

273
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,640
Don’t be afraid.

274
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:28,760
For our dream.

275
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,560
So shall we go?

276
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,440
Let’s go.

277
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,000
Not too far, right?

278
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,080
Not far.

279
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:33,120
Let’s go.

280
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,240
Leave it here in case someone else gets lost.

281
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,280
Yeah.

282
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,320
Let’s keep going, everyone.

283
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:49,160
Thank you for shopping with us.

284
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:52,480
After the face mask, apply the moisturizer cream.

285
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:57,520
Thank you so much. JK Beauty, everything in one stop at Found&Found.

286
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,520
Thank you.

287
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:07,760
What are you doing, All-New?

288
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,760
Exercising, obviously.

289
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:12,760
I’m about to have some smoothie.

290
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:15,440
For that?

291
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:19,320
And what have you found on Mr. Glam.

292
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:21,120
This time for sure...

293
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:25,120
I’m going to rip off your mask, Glam!

294
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,920
I’ve got one too!

295
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:32,920
Shit.

296
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:36,520
I think you hacked so much your brain fried.

297
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:39,120
Give me your phone. I want to see you Line application.

298
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:42,720
Hey, who lets people see their private stuff?

299
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,960
I’m not looking at your chats.

300
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,160
I want to see the group with Mr. Glam in it.

301
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,160
Yeah, yeah, fine.

302
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:59,040
Shit, Kreetha.

303
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,040
Your dad’s calling.

304
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,760
Hi, Dad.

305
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:10,800
Kreetha, do you have thirty thousand for me?

306
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,880
I really need it, son. I have to pay them.

307
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:13,800
Again, Dad?

308
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,200
Our chicken couldn’t beat theirs.

309
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,680
We lost completely, Kreetha.

310
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:20,400
I don’t know what else to do.

311
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,280
Transfer it for me, please, Kreetha.

312
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:23,720
Oh, Dad...

313
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:26,720
Please hurry. Tonight, okay? Thank you so much, son.

314
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:38,120
Hey, I’m fine. It's okay.

315
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,400
C'mon. Let’s keep digging up info on Glam.

316
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:49,800
Let’s see. Who’s in the group?

317
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:53,200
Shit. That name is ancient. P-Chai.

318
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,160
No, All-New. That’s Chai. Our Chai.

319
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,560
Oh, okay.

320
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,680
And who’s this?

321
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:01,760
Cha-ba. (crazy)

322
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,440
You’re the crazy one. That’s Chaba.

323
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,880
Oh, Chaba.

324
00:14:05,880 --> 00:14:07,200
This one’s Sky.

325
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,200
Hey, did this guy just leave monkhood?

326
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,680
Do we have someone who ordained in our office?

327
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,280
Here, TidGift.

328
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,320
Oh god, that’s Tid-Gift.

329
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:16,560
Oh, Tid-Gift.

330
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:20,560
Ah, this “G” guy.

331
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:22,720
Goong, the pimple-squeezer...

332
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:25,560
Goong up your ass, that's Mr. Glam.

333
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:26,560
I'm just kidding.

334
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,560
Shit, and who the hell is “P”?

335
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,560
Huh? Let’s see.

336
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:35,960
Hey!

337
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,360
We’ll need to search for info.

338
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,960
I’ve never seen this person before.

339
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:54,880
Siri, walk faster. What are you waiting for?

340
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,920
I’m tired, okay?

341
00:14:56,920 --> 00:15:00,920
Ever since we entered this jungle, you’ve been complaining nonstop.

342
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,240
Well, how can I not complain?

343
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:05,520
I’m Siri, not a porter.

344
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:08,080
Look at you, walking so light and free.

345
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,240
If you’re so free, how about helping carry something?

346
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:13,520
Stop complaining and let’s call it even.

347
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,960
Even for what?

348
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:18,280
For making me dress like this to go hiking.

349
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,760
Hey, I googled it.

350
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:23,120
Everyone dresses like this when they go to the jungle.

351
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:26,080
After seeing Lord Grandfather, why don’t we stop by a festival?

352
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,360
Wonderfruit, maybe? Perfect for you.

353
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,920
I was being sarcastic.

354
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:34,920
But seriously, are we going to the Indian subcontinent or something?

355
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,680
Why is it so far?

356
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:40,280
Don’t you know the good stuff is always deep in the jungle?

357
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,360
We’re already as deep as it gets.

358
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:44,520
Do you really think Lord Grandfather is even real?

359
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,760
Talking like that is disrespectful, you know.

360
00:15:46,760 --> 00:15:50,520
Well, Mr. Yuttachai said he exists, so he must.

361
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:53,680
Hey, I see something on that tree.

362
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:57,680
Hey, Siri! In the jungle you’re not supposed to mention anything you see.

363
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:59,200
It’ll follow you home.

364
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,160
Okay.

365
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,240
Hey, I see...

366
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,240
I said don’t say it!

367
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:14,720
Siri, can you check what I just stepped on?

368
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:17,840
Madam...

369
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,600
What?

370
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:19,200
Madam...

371
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:22,680
What, Siri, what is it?

372
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:23,680
A watermelon.

373
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,360
A watermelon?

374
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:30,960
Siri, Siri, get it off. Get it off me.

375
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:34,720
C'mon, Madam, just keep walking and it’ll fall off.

376
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,440
Let’s go. Hurry.

377
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,440
Siri!

378
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:38,840
Hurry up, Madam.

379
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:43,840
I’m scared, Siri. I’m really scared.

380
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:50,400
Ladies and gentlemen, welcome on board...

381
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:52,960
to Glamorous Airline.

382
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,760
And next will be the demonstration…

383
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:57,040
That’s right. Up next is our review of flying...

384
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:01,000
with Glamorous Airline.

385
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:03,960
Hello, everyone.

386
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,400
Okay, okay...

387
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,800
Now this will be the safety demonstration.

388
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:12,320
Your life vest is located under your seat, which…

389
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:15,760
This seat? It’s so soft and wide. So soft!

390
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:19,760
The air-conditioning is freezing cold. Wow, the aisle is so wide.

391
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:23,720
And the cabin smell? So fragrant.

392
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,800
I’m really impressed.

393
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,880
Excuse me.

394
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:31,240
We’re currently demonstrating the use of emergency equipment.

395
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,880
Please shut your mouths...

396
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,880
oh, please lower your voices.

397
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:41,800
Thank you for lowering your voices and shutting your mouths.

398
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:44,080
Now, let’s continue with the demonstration.

399
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:46,800
Your life vest is under your seat,

400
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,000
and to use it…

401
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,320
This is so cute!

402
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,600
Thank you all from the bottom of our hearts...

403
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,600
for flying with Glamorous Airline.

404
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:06,520
You’re still not shutting up, huh?

405
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:11,720
Do you want to be a mummy?

406
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:15,520
Then sit quietly, please. Thank you.

407
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:21,880
And that’s how we deal with rude passengers.

408
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:25,120
Rude, vile and trashy.

409
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,120
Glamorous Airline is happy to serve you.

410
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,240
Shut it.

411
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:37,120
Excuse me, my kid lost a toy.

412
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:38,880
I can’t find it, what should I do?

413
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:42,880
What's this? The plane hasn’t even taken off and there are already a thousand problems.

414
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:54,720
I'm exhausted!

415
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:57,640
Hey, that tree!

416
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,880
That rock...wait, are we going in circles?

417
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,640
Don't tell me...

418
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:04,640
we're lost!

419
00:19:07,080 --> 00:19:08,680
Are we really lost?

420
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:12,120
No way. We must find Lord Grandfather.

421
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:13,960
Wait, are we still finding him?

422
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,520
We will see him!

423
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,400
How about we set up a tent here?

424
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,400
Right, right, it's with you.

425
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:22,960
Where is it?

426
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:23,560
Here!

427
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:24,680
Alright, let's do it!

428
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,080
We’ll sleep comfortably.

429
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:26,720
Yeah.

430
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,000
So we can finally go see Lord Grandfather.

431
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,880
We’ll start our journey again tomorrow, okay?

432
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,240
Here.

433
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,760
Sigma’s one foot can’t even fit in here.

434
00:19:35,760 --> 00:19:38,760
Kungkaew, is this a tent or a doghouse?

435
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,000
I don’t know, I ordered it online. It said it's for seven...

436
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,000
A seven-year-old, maybe?

437
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:48,760
This is so stressful.

438
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,920
Everyone, don’t panic.

439
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:53,320
We need to do a stress-relief activity.

440
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,680
While we’re literally fleeing for our lives.

441
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:56,520
How?

442
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,080
I have a stress-relief prop for everyone.

443
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:58,680
What?

444
00:19:58,680 --> 00:19:59,560
I’m scared.

445
00:19:59,560 --> 00:19:59,880
Where is it?

446
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:00,600
What is it?

447
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:01,680
Here. I found it.

448
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,600
This.

449
00:20:02,600 --> 00:20:04,200
Whoa!

450
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,080
Oh, you’re gonna lay it out to sleep on, right?

451
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,720
Nope. That’s too basic.

452
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:10,640
Let’s find creative ways to de-stress.

453
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:14,640
Let’s see what this piece of cloth can become.

454
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:18,400
Hold on a sec.

455
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:23,560
Suchata Chuangsi, Miss World Thailand.

456
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:25,200
No, that's not it.

457
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:25,880
No?

458
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:27,840
No, no!

459
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:28,800
It’s this one.

460
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,800
Huh? What are you doing, Kungkaew?

461
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:36,680
If Father would just let me go to the human world, that’d be nice.

462
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:38,280
Whoa!

463
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:39,280
Guess! Guess!

464
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,560
It's from Aladdin.

465
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:42,920
No, it's from Little Mermaid!

466
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:43,760
Oh.

467
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,720
Listen up. It’s my turn now.

468
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:46,720
There.

469
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,200
Hey, don’t get aggressive.

470
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:52,280
I’m stressed. I can’t take it anymore.

471
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:54,640
We have to survive.

472
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,520
Can we sit and calm down first?

473
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,120
Can we?

474
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:58,880
Of course, Chaba.

475
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,880
No!

476
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,840
I’m scared. We can’t survive in this jungle.

477
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:03,880
In the middle of the night.

478
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:04,920
Yeah, I’m scared too.

479
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,200
You’re stressed right now.

480
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:09,440
Sit down, calm yourself. Take deep breaths.

481
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,720
Oh!

482
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:12,360
What’s that sound?

483
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:12,880
Hey!

484
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,400
That sound...

485
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:19,400
It’s a crested bulbul.

486
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:22,200
Ugh, no!

487
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:22,920
This isn’t funny.

488
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:23,200
Oh, no?

489
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,200
No!

490
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:28,440
What’s that sound?

491
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:29,680
That sound...

492
00:21:29,680 --> 00:21:33,680
It’s the sound of firecrackers from Auntie’s house.

493
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:36,360
That's enough!

494
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:36,960
No.

495
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,960
That’s not it.

496
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:41,600
Oh, oh! That sound...

497
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,280
That sound...

498
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,080
What sound?

499
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,880
Jelly takes over Surin!...

500
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:46,880
Anyone who hears it will want some.

501
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:48,760
Chewy, tasty, so soft on the tongue.

502
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:49,760
Go tell Dad...

503
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:53,160
We’ve watched way too much TikTok.

504
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,560
Now we’re all stressed out.

505
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:55,760
I’m scared!

506
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:56,640
I’m really scared!

507
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:57,480
What do we do?

508
00:21:57,480 --> 00:22:01,480
Listen. Right now we need to sit and take deep breaths.

509
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:04,960
And we'll survive.

510
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:06,960
Okay.

511
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:11,160
Hey, is that the sound of...

512
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:13,160
A forest spirit!

513
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:21,160
A forest spirit!

514
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,520
It's Chaba! Chaba!

515
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,000
Hi there.

516
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:54,360
He's still crying.

517
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:58,360
Tid-Gift, if you don't know how to do it. Back off, I'll handle this.

518
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,200
I'm here. I'm here.

519
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:08,880
I thought you said you could handle it.

520
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,400
I've never had a kid before.

521
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:14,160
Back off, I'll handle it.

522
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:16,360
How about this, little boy?

523
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:18,880
If you stop crying...

524
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:21,800
I have some candy for you.

525
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:25,560
Would you like to have it?

526
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,560
Okay.

527
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:34,800
So? How's that? Kids love candy.

528
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,800
It's easy-peasy. You guys just couldn't think of it.

529
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:47,880
This is not tasty! This is not tasty!

530
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,920
I thought you said kids loved candy...

531
00:23:54,920 --> 00:23:56,320
You couldn't do it either.

532
00:23:56,320 --> 00:23:57,320
So how's that?

533
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,720
What an evil kid!

534
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:13,880
Guys!

535
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,120
I think this is not right.

536
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:17,120
Why don't we switch the spots?

537
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:18,120
Alright, alright.

538
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:25,240
I think it's still not right.

539
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:26,080
No?

540
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:26,520
Still?

541
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:27,280
Alright, let's do it again.

542
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,280
Alright, alright.

543
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:36,280
I think it's still the same. Do we need to switch again?

544
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:38,440
It's alright. If the kid loves it, that's all that matters.

545
